      • overlap

        static boolean overlap​(java.util.Scanner sc)
        The method takes a scanner as the input, reads in the position of each point of each line. Given the positions, the method sees whether there exists at least one point lies on another line. If there exists, the lines overlap. Assumption: two lines with only one point overlaps are considered overlap.
        Parameters:
        sc - : the scanner that takes console input of the coordinates of two lines
        Returns:
        true if the two lines overlap
